events.text:
Day 813
This will be my final entry.
The moon carrots are gone.
The moon bunny has eaten them all and I’ve depleted my stockpile.
There has been no word from Earth, from home.
Either no one knows or no one cares that I’m still up here.
I’m not sure what happens next, but I have a good idea.
The carrots are gone.
I feel the beast’s eyes on me.
It knows I’m in here.
It knows.
